{
  "id": "smallhold-b89",
  "title": "Phase 1: Actor Publication",
  "description": "Publish this server's identity to the fediverse: actor documents, WebFinger, NodeInfo, host-meta, and the ability to resolve and cache remote actors. This is the derisk phase — get a live Mastodon instance to fetch your WebFinger and display your profile before writing a single HTTP handler for the client API.",
  "design": "Content-type negotiation on /users/:username: AP doc for activity+json or ld+json, HTML redirect for browsers, AP doc also for application/json (Pleroma compat). activitypub-federation crate for HTTP signature handling on outbound GETs.",
  "acceptance_criteria": "curl of actor URI returns valid AP document; mastodon.social can fetch WebFinger and display the profile; a remote actor can be resolved and stored in remote_accounts; signed GETs work against GoToSocial (which requires authorized fetch)",
